So I think I discovered a secret about crow pose.

I thought I was supposed to shove my knees as far into my armpits as possible. And because I'm rather flexible in some parts of my body, I was really hiking them up way too far!

The back of my arms used to hurt a lot and I couldn't find a stable posture because my knees kept slipping over the muscles in my upper arms, to either side.

Now if I put my knees a whole lot lower, around about 1/3 of my upper arms, I'm able to find some amount of more flat space where my muscles are not in the way and all of a sudden the phrase 'a shelf for your knees' makes sense! So I think it's about finding that place in your body.
